<subSubSection pageId="153" pageNumber="154" type="note">
<paragraph pageId="153" pageNumber="154">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="153" pageNumber="154">
Lindroth (1961a: 29) retained 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">brevoorti</emphasis>
as &quot;a weak subspecies, at most.&quot; I studied several specimens from Newfoundland, the Maritimes, and Quebec, including Anticosti Island, and found no structural differences between populations of the forms 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">nitidicollis</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">brevoorti</emphasis>
except for the fact that adults of the 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">nitidicollis</emphasis>
form are on average slightly larger than those of the 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">brevoorti</emphasis>
form.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
